        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Digging a bit in git history, It seems this was used (and is still used in the unchecked `Makefile.msc` and `Makefile.unix` ) to determine where the header files live. The `Makefile` changed and now that is done via \r\n```\r\nINCDIR := $(shell $(PYTHON) -c \"from distutils import sysconfig; print(sysconfig.get_python_inc())\")\r\n```\r\n\r\nAll the uses of distutils in that Makefile should be refactored to avoid using distutils since it is deprecated and changed to \r\n```\r\nINCDIR := $(shell $(PYTHON) -c \"import sysconfig; print(sysconfig.get_config_var('INCLUDEPY'))\")\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
